The comment says: "must check name slot and NOT property name, as only former is lower-case in case-insensitive case". So they should compare `key` with the key stored at index i-1 (the even index). Because in case-insensitive property lookup, the keys are stored in lower case for case-insensitive matching, while `prop.getName()` returns the original name which may have different case.

Therefore, the fix is to change the comparison to use the key stored at `_hashArea[i-1]` (the string key) rather than `prop.getName()`.

